EELTAIL

by Mick Green

Click here for  backstory.

Clear now is the memory of how things turned so sour... a hole in the ground... falling... then waking up here, bewildered and confused. Looking up - sure enough - there is the opening high above, and a carefully prepared pack full of essential items is missing!

Damp dingy tunnels

The cobblestone floor has green moss on it here and there.
You can see a hole and a heavy door of iron (secured by a hefty padlock and some bolts).
You can go northeast or in.
> northeast

> northeast

A chamber carved out of the earth
You can see a large wooden pillar.
You can go southwest, east, northeast or to the south where a slimy slope ascends.
> look at ring

> look at ring

This iron band girths the wooden pillar and looks as strong and tight as the day it was fitted. The pillar itself though does have a few cracks, some large enough to make it possible to get your fingers behind the ring - you notice a piece of wire wrapped loosely around it.
> take wire

> take wire

You take the wire.
> southwest

> southwest

Damp dingy tunnels

The cobblestone floor has green moss on it here and there.
You can see a hole and a heavy door of iron (secured by a hefty padlock and some bolts).
You can go northeast or in.
> open padlock

> open padlock

You use the wire to open the padlock...

The padlock springs open!
> take padlock

> take padlock

You take the padlock.
> open bolts

> open bolts

You open the bolts.

Free of its restraints, the door swings slightly open, bringing with it a slight change in the air and a new kind of silence... This silence though is quickly broken by a terrifying 'ROAR!' delivered by something lurking behind the door! You instinctively know that if you do not flee, and fast, you will certainly be killed by this thing you have unleashed!
