                                  e . . . . . !     Your slide abruptly ends and you find your balance.

A chamber carved out of the earth
You can see a large wooden pillar.
You can go southwest, east, northeast or to the south where a slimy slope ascends.

You can hear the ferocious monster - whatever it is - charging after you!

There is a gruesome chain being dragged jerkily across the floor, rattling noisily and whipping up dust.
> padlock chain to ring

> padlock chain to ring

You snap the padlock shut, joining together  the ring and the chain.

A few moments of straining ensue, wherein, you wonder what will give first - the padlock, the chain, or the ring. Shockingly, the entire pillar itself is dislodged with a thunderous crack! It topples, leaving the chamber sounding very unstable and begins to be dragged eastward as the beast starts moving again... Time to flee once more!

some heavy debris from above hits you! (-2 health)
> northeast

> northeast

A wide hallway of chalk
You can go southwest or northeast.

The noise of the terrifying creature sends echoes scurrying through the tunnel around you!

> northeast

> northeast

A circular cavern of great height and depth
You are standing on a jutting, flat ridge, looking out upon an empty void.
Looking down and up, it appears certain death would result from any attempt at descent or ascent.
You can go southwest.

You are caught by huge, powerful hands...

Unaware of the looming, empty void ahead of it, the beast sails straight over the edge, its gigantic hands, human-like in form, tightening still more around your upper body!
You become rigid with fear as you both begin to plummet with increasing speed, deeper and deeper into the depths...
The eerie silence is broken by a sickening slam! You are ejected from the beast's grip and fall into a roll across the hard floor, coming to a stop some distance away.
You remain still, lying on your side and staring across at the static heap of black fur - the hulking form of the monster - a haze of dust in orbit around it. You wait for the pain to begin, but amazingly you clamber to your feet more or less unharmed! The beast on the other hand was not nearly so fortunate, taking the full brunt of the impact for both of you.

