> close door

> close door

On the darkened floor, thin lines of light present the outline of a trapdoor!
> open trapdoor

> open trapdoor

The open trapdoor in the floor presents a long and reckless descent by means of a slippery chute!
> down

> down

You have slid down into the lair of the red dragon
A charred smell greets your nostrils. Flame and cinder patch the ground and through the haze, You see the massive shape of a dragon turning majestically around to face its guest.
You can see the large and looming shape of the red dragon and the hole high above that you slid through.
The dragon's laughter booms around its lair: "Ho! Ho! Ho! Ho! Nice of you to drop in you scrawny little thief!"
> fold page into mermaid

> fold page into mermaid

You make the page into a mermaid.
The mermaid increases in size until she is around three meters long! All the while, water from some unknown source, pours into the place, rising quickly up your legs!
"There you are you wicked old wretch!" says the mermaid, "The time for your fire to be put out is long overdue!"
The dragon has only time to shriek in terror before a massive wave rushes in and drenches everything in his lair!
After this the mermaid is gone; you are wet but surprisingly content and the dragon coughs out a barrel's worth of water before dying...
> look at clutter

> look at clutter

There is a chest full of gold coins!
You also unearth a charred journal of some sort.
There is nothing else among the burned mass that remotely exites you.
> put chest in bag

> put chest in bag

chest full of gold coins bagged. Does it surprise you that the bag is still empty?
