A cave entrance
You are in a cave looking out from a great height.
You can see Galverzalk.
You can go west or northwest.
Galverzalk looks at you with disdane, "So thief! You are the one who has my parchment!" He
throws his arms out in a whipping motion. There is a flash of light and a multitude of goblins appear all around you! At first they are as confused as you but quickly adjust.
'To the dungeon with the intruder!' shouts Galverzalk and you are powerless to resist as the goblins drag you away. You are taken into the arched area and from there through many twists and turns and down strange dark tunnels - all this time your belongings are being stolen and rifled by the ugly brutes - until you arrive at a very strong iron door. It is unlocked and you are thrown inside...

