> place crown on dwarf

> place crown on dwarf

The moment the crown is placed on the head of the stone dwarf colour returns to his flesh and clothing! He stands up and fixes his gaze upon you.

"I am Merlon the ancient king of this mountain - and ancient I am! I think so greedy a king was I that old EELTAIL prefered playing host to dragons and goblins rather than put up with me any longer.

You see, it wasn't dragons and goblins that caused our end but my greed and an unlikely act of generosity was the only thing that would lift the curse - one I thought would never come, especially from one such as you. Oh yes I've been well aware of your activity in this mountain. I've been fully aware af all goings on though as static as a rock and I could scarcely believe it when you placed that crown on my head. If I wasn't such a hard hearted old rogue you might even see a tear roll down my cheek.

Now I walk out of here alone and with nothing - and I am thankful! This crown means nothing to me now so keep it, but know that by honoring me today you have secured a more valuable treasure for yourself in that you have placed honor upon your own head in a way that many of your kind never will. Here, take also this medal," Merlon removes a magnificent piece of jewelry from his neck and places it over your head, "It is a dwarven medal for the rewarding of the stout-hearted. It is a treasure greater than any other but one you will never wish to part with."

Merlon leaves the room, no doubt to start a new life and find a place to belong in a world he does not know. You wonder whether this king who has relinquished his crown, will also be able to relinquish his habit of giving long speeches and not letting other people talk but then he has been silent for such a long time.

